### Custom Expect Message in Playwright Python

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-assertions-csharp-java-python.md

Specify a custom expect message as the second argument to the expect function in Playwright Python tests. When an assertion fails, the custom message is displayed along with the actual value and call log, improving test failure readability and debugging.

```python
expect(page.get_by_text("Name"), "should be logged in").to_be_visible()
```

--------------------------------

### Add Custom Error Messages to Playwright `expect` Assertions (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/release-notes-js.md

Illustrates adding a custom message as the second argument to `expect()` or `expect.soft()`. This message displays in the test report upon assertion failure, providing clearer debugging context.

```javascript
await expect(page.locator('text=Name'), 'should be logged in').toBeVisible();
```

