### Configure Playwright expect Assertions (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testconfig.md

This snippet demonstrates how to configure the `expect` assertion library within Playwright's `TestConfig`. It sets a global timeout for assertions and customizes `toMatchSnapshot` behavior for pixel difference thresholds. This configuration affects all tests using `expect` assertions.

```js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  expect: {
    timeout: 10000,
    toMatchSnapshot: {
      maxDiffPixels: 10,
    },
  },
});
```

