### Compare Expected and Actual Test Status in afterEach Hook - JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testinfo.md

This snippet demonstrates how to use TestInfo.expectedStatus and TestInfo.status properties to detect when a test does not run as expected. It uses an afterEach hook to log a message when the actual status differs from the expected status, which is useful for monitoring test behavior.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.afterEach(async ({}, testInfo) => {
  if (testInfo.status !== testInfo.expectedStatus)
    console.log(`${testInfo.title} did not run as expected!`);
});
```

