### Skip a Test in Playwright using test.skip

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-annotations-js.md

Marks a test as skipped using the test.skip() annotation. Playwright will not execute this test. This is useful when a test is not applicable or temporarily needs to be excluded from the test run.

```javascript
test.skip('skip this test', async ({ page }) => {
  // This test is not run
});
```

--------------------------------

### Set Playwright Maximum Test Failures

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testconfig.md

Specifies the maximum number of test failures allowed across the entire test suite. Once this limit is reached, test execution will stop and exit with an error. Setting this to zero disables the behavior, allowing all tests to run regardless of failures.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  maxFailures: process.env.CI ? 1 : 0,
});
```

