### Checking for Soft Assertion Failures in Playwright

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-assertions-js.md

This snippet shows how to explicitly check if any soft assertions have failed during test execution by inspecting the `test.info().errors` array. This allows for conditional logic based on the success or failure of soft assertions, for instance, preventing further execution if critical soft assertions have failed.

```javascript
// Make a few checks that will not stop the test when failed...
await expect.soft(page.getByTestId('status')).toHaveText('Success');
await expect.soft(page.getByTestId('eta')).toHaveText('1 day');

// Avoid running further if there were soft assertion failures.
expect(test.info().errors).toHaveLength(0);
```

