### Configure Playwright Snapshot Expectation Ignoring

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testconfig.md

Determines whether snapshot expectations, such as `expect(value).toMatchSnapshot()` and `await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot()`, should be skipped during test execution. This is often conditionally enabled, for example, when running tests locally but not in CI.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  ignoreSnapshots: !process.env.CI,
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Playwright `expect` Defaults (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-assertions-js.md

Explains how to create a pre-configured `expect` instance using `expect.configure`. This allows setting default options like `timeout` or `soft` for subsequent assertions, promoting reusability and consistency across tests.

```javascript
const slowExpect = expect.configure({ timeout: 10000 });
await slowExpect(locator).toHaveText('Submit');
```

```javascript
const softExpect = expect.configure({ soft: true });
await softExpect(locator).toHaveText('Submit');
```

