### Perform Async Playwright assertions with `expect` and `toHaveTitle`

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/writing-tests-js.md

This code demonstrates using Playwright's asynchronous `expect` function with a matcher like `toHaveTitle` to wait for a specific condition. This approach makes tests non-flaky and resilient by waiting until the expected state, such as a page title, is met.

```js
await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/Playwright/);
```

--------------------------------

### Annotate a Playwright Test with a Single Issue URL

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-annotations-js.md

This snippet demonstrates how to add a single annotation to a Playwright test. The annotation includes a 'type' (e.g., 'issue') and a 'description' (e.g., a URL), providing additional context visible in reporters like Playwright's built-in HTML reporter.

```js
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('test login page', {
  annotation: {
    type: 'issue',
    description: 'https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/23180',
  },
}, async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});
```

