### Override Playwright expect assertion timeout for individual assertions

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-timeouts-js.md

This example shows how to specify a timeout for a single `expect` assertion by passing a `timeout` option directly to the assertion method, such as `toHaveText`. This overrides the global expect timeout for that specific assertion.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('example', async ({ page }) => {
  await expect(locator).toHaveText('hello', { timeout: 10_000 });
});
```

