### Add Custom Messages to Playwright `expect` Assertions (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-assertions-js.md

Demonstrates how to provide a custom message as a second argument to the `expect` function in Playwright. This message is displayed in reporters for both passing and failing assertions, offering more context. It also shows its application with `expect.soft` for soft assertions.

```javascript
await expect(page.getByText('Name'), 'should be logged in').toBeVisible();
```

```javascript
expect.soft(value, 'my soft assertion').toBe(56);
```

