### Retry Code Block Until Assertions Pass with Playwright expect().toPass() (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/release-notes-js.md

Demonstrates the use of `expect(async () => { ... }).toPass()` to retry a block of asynchronous code until all assertions within it successfully pass. This feature is crucial for testing eventual consistency and asynchronous operations.

```javascript
await expect(async () => {
  const response = await page.request.get('https://api.example.com');
  await expect(response).toBeOK();
}).toPass();
```

