### Configure Maximum Failures in Playwright Config - JavaScript/TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-parallel-js.md

Sets the maxFailures configuration option in playwright.config.ts to limit test failures. This example conditionally sets the limit to 10 in CI environments while leaving it unlimited locally. The configuration uses the defineConfig utility from @playwright/test for type safety.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Limit the number of failures on CI to save resources
  maxFailures: process.env.CI ? 10 : undefined,
});
```
